Template 1: Organized Business Planning
ROLE: [type of expert needed]
TASK: [what to create or plan]
CONTEXT: [business model, target customers, key operational details]
REQUIREMENTS: [must-haves, preferences, standards to maintain]
BUDGET CONSTRAINTS: [spending limits, timeline, financial goals]

When to Use: when business information is scattered and needs clear organization
Coffee Cart Use: organized initial business notes and expansion planning

Template 2: Guided Information Gathering
Ask questions one at a time about [topic area].
Start with [first aspect], then move to [other aspects in sequence].
Remember these key details: [constraints and context].
After collecting answers, create [deliverable].

When to Use: when building comprehensive plans through systematic questioning
Coffee Cart Use: gathered complete setup details for launch planning


*************************************************************************************

Category: Few-Shot Prompting
When to Use: Need consistent formatting across multiple communications
Template: "Here are examples of our [type] format:

Example 1: '[specific example with desired format]'
Example 2: '[another example following same format]'

Now create [new content] using this same format."

What worked: Used for artist invitations with professional format examples
Planning application: Artist invitations, sponsor communications, and vendor outreach
Key benefit: Ensures professional consistency without starting from scratch each time
